&lt;p&gt;NURSING ASSISTANTS BAND 2 Laburnum Ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking for a new challenge? Wanting to make a difference?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit full time Nursing Assistants to join our friendly, supportive team on the Medical Unit at the Horton hospital. The unit practices a 12 hour shift system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be enthusiastic and motivated, working as part of the team in delivering the highest standard of care to treat our patients with dignity, compassion and respect&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to demonstrate excellent communication skills and the ability to work within the Multi Disciplinary Team . Previous experience and possession of the Care certificate desirable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will actively encourage your personal and professional development through training opportunities within the Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits welcome&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 15-Nov-2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tim Lewitt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;alison.vannozzi@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01295 229844&lt;/p&gt;
